    "what_description": "Trigonotis doormanensis is a species of flowering plant in the family Boraginaceae. It has a perennial habit and is characterized by its stems that are 10-30 cm tall, glabrous, and 4-angled. The leaves are 1-4 cm long, alternate, glabrous, and linear-lanceolate to linear-oblanceolate, with a glabrous petiole that is 0.5-2.5 cm long. The inflorescence is a terminal spike with small flowers, which have a glabrous calyx that is 2-3 mm long and 5-lobed, and a corolla that is 3-4 mm long and 5-lobed. The fruits are small, glabrous, and 4-6 mm long, each containing 4-6 seeds.",
