    "uses": "Trigonotis doormanensis has been reported to have various medicinal properties, with studies indicating its potential in treating digestive issues and inflammation. The plant is also said to have antimicrobial and antifungal properties, making it a possible natural remedy for infections. Research suggests that Trigonotis doormanensis may have antioxidant and anti-inflammatory effects, which could contribute to its potential health benefits. However, more research is needed to fully understand the plant's medicinal properties and its effects on human health. Further studies are essential to explore the plant's potential applications in traditional medicine.",
