    "benefits": "Trigonotis doormanensis is believed to have various health benefits due to its unique properties. The plant is thought to possess antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, which may help protect against cell damage and reduce inflammation in the body. Its leaves are often used in traditional medicine to treat respiratory issues, such as coughs and bronchitis. Additionally, Trigonotis doormanensis may have antimicrobial properties, helping to prevent infections and promote wound healing. Further research is needed to fully understand the plant's potential health benefits and confirm its efficacy.",
    "parts": "Trigonotis doormanensis is a plant species, but specific information about its medicinal parts is not readily available in my database. However, the plant family Pedicularis is a well-known source of medicinal compounds, and some species within the same family may have similar properties. Further research is needed to determine the exact medicinal parts of Trigonotis doormanensis, if any. In general, various plant species within the same family may have similar medicinal properties. More information about Trigonotis doormanensis is required to provide a detailed answer.",
    "intro": "Trigonotis doormanensis, also known as Doorman's trigonotis, is a species of flowering plant in the family Boraginaceae. This plant has been traditionally used for its medicinal properties, offering potential health benefits such as anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial effects, which can aid in reducing inflammation and improving overall well-being. The bioactive constituents of Trigonotis doormanensis include flavonoids, phenolic acids, and terpenoids, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. In traditional medicine, Trigonotis doormanensis is often made into herbal teas, infusions, and tinctures, which are commonly used to treat various health conditions."
